  <thing id="fMDsrmTend" name="Disarming Tendrils" description="{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Agile Tendrils, Spell Focus (conjuration or transmutation), ability to cast a tendril spell (a spell that entangles or grapples foes).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action you can direct a tendril spell you have cast to attempt to remove an item from one target of your choice already entangled or grappled by the spell. This functions as a Disarm or Steal* combat maneuver (as appropriate to the item you attempt to take), but your CMB is equal to (caster level + tendril spell level). The concentration required to perform this maneuver does provoke an attack of opportunity from creatures that threaten you, unless you have the appropriate feat (Improved Disarm or Improved Steal). You gain the benefit of any feats that give you additional options when using these combat maneuvers (such as Greater Steal).\n\nAn item disarmed or stolen is held in place by the tendril spell. As a move action, you may have the tendril spell hand any items it has taken to creatures within or adjacent to the area of the spell.\n\n*Indicated a combat maneuver found in the Advanced Player&#146;s Guide." compset="Feat" summary="Your tendril spells can grab items away from targets" uniqueness="useronce">
