  <thing id="fMDstbTend" name="Disturbing Tendrils" description="{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Agile Tendrils, Spell Focus (conjuration or transmutation), ability to cast a tendril spell (a spell that entangles or grapples foes).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action you can direct a tendril spell you have cast to threaten and rudely prod one target of your choice already entangled or grappled by the spell. You may make an Intimidate or Spellcraft check to demoralize that target (as the demoralize option of the Intimidate skill). For each consecutive round you use this action on the same target you gain a +1 cumulative bonus to your Intimidate or Spellcraft check, to a maximum bonus equal to the level of the tendril spell used." compset="Feat" summary="Your tendril spells can make threatening gestures, prod its targets uncomfortably, and general act in a disturbing and discomforting manner" uniqueness="useronce">
