  <thing id="fMHrssTend" name="Harassing Tendrils" description="{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Agile Tendrils, Spell Focus (conjuration or transmutation), ability to cast a tendril spell (a spell that entangles or grapples foes).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action you can direct a tendril spell you have cast to attempt to harass one target of your choice either within the spell&#146;s area or adjacent to it. This functions as a Dirty Trick* or Trip combat maneuver, but your CMB is equal to (caster level + tendril spell level). The concentration required to perform this maneuver does provoke an attack of opportunity from creatures that threaten you, unless you have the appropriate feat (Improved Dirty Trick or Improved Trip). You gain the benefit of any feats that give you additional options when using these combat maneuvers (such as Greater Trip).\n\n*Indicated a combat maneuver found in the Advanced Player&#146;s Guide." compset="Feat" summary="Your tendril spells can make trouble even for creatures not grabbed by them" uniqueness="useronce">
